Dual booting ubuntu with Windows 10.

Use UNETBOOTIN software to create live USB

Use FAT32 encoding

Do not force UEFI installation 

After installation (ubuntu) if windows boot option is missing, perform following terminal commands while in ubuntu:

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:yannubuntu/boot-repair 
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y boot-repair && boot-repair

If frequent crashing occurs, go to Software & Updates, Additional Drivers,  - set all options to proprietary

